Additionally, Lexi Rabe portrays [[Morgan Stark (Earth-199999)|Morgan Stark]]. {{WP|Ross Marquand}} reprises the role of [[Johann Schmidt (Earth-TRN734)|Red Skull/Stonekeeper]]. Co-director [[Joe Russo]] (credited as Gozie Agbo) and Thanos co-creator [[Jim Starlin]] cameo as grieving men. [[Cassandra Lang (Earth-199999)|Cassie Lang]] in 2023 is now portrayed by {{WP|Emma Fuhrmann}}. {{WP|Michael James Shaw|Michael Shaw}} and {{WP|Terry Notary}} reprise their roles as [[Corvus Glaive (Earth-TRN734)|Corvus Glaive]] and [[Cull Obsidian (Earth-TRN734)|Cull Obsidian]], respectively. {{WP|Kerry Condon}} returns to voice [[F.R.I.D.A.Y. (Earth-199999)|F.R.I.D.A.Y.]] Ben Sakamoto, Ava Russo, and Cade Woodward portray [[Cooper Barton (Earth-199999)|Cooper]], [[Lila Barton (Earth-199999)|Lila Barton]], and [[Nathaniel Barton (Earth-199999)|Nathaniel Barton]], respectively. [[Stan Lee]] cameos as a hippie driver. ''{{WP|Community (TV series)|Community}}'' alumni {{WP|Yvette Nicole Brown}} and {{WP|Ken Jeong}} make cameo appearances in the film. {{WP|Callan Mulvey}} reprises his ''The Winter Soldier'' role [[Jack Rollins (Earth-TRN732)|Agent Jack Rollins]]. Co-director [[Anthony Russo]]'s son Julian, niece Lia, and nephew Auggie portray Hulk fans. {{WP|Ty Simpkins}} reprises his role as [[Harley Keener (Earth-199999)|Harley Keener]] from ''Iron Man 3''. {{WP|Matthew Berry}} cameos as a SHIELD agent.

{{WP|Carrie Coon}} doesn't reprise her voice role as [[Proxima Midnight (Earth-TRN734)|Proxima Midnight]], but {{WP|Monique Ganderton}} still provides the motion capture for the character. {{WP|Katherine Langford}} shot a scene as a grown-up Morgan Stark, but the scene wasn't included in the final cut of the film.{{r|{{cite web|url= https://www.indiewire.com/2019/05/katherine-langfords-avengers-endgame-role-revealed-1202131589/|title= Katherine Langfordâ€™s Cut â€˜Avengers: Endgameâ€™ Character Revealed, Plus Why Her Scene Got Axed|work= THR|last= Sharf|first= Zack|date= May 6, 2019|accessdate=January 11, 2020}}}} {{WP|Paul Bettany}} doesn't reprise his role as the [[Vision (Earth-199999)|Vision]], although previously indicating he would.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/paul-bettany-interview-manhunt-unabomber-avengers-infinity-war#marvel|title=Paul Bettany on â€˜Manhunt: Unabomberâ€™, Understanding Ted Kaczynski, and â€˜Avengers: Infinity Warâ€™|first=Christina|last=Radish|work=Collider|date=15 August 2017|accessdate=31 August 2017}}</ref>

